# [MLS](../wg/mls.html)

## Summary

The Messaging Layer Security (MLS) Working Group met at IETF 126 to discuss the status of active working group drafts, progress post-quantum (PQ) cipher suites, evaluate proposed extensions, and discuss decentralized deployments and architectural scaling under PQ constraints. 

Key advancements included addressing KDF specification issues for PQ ciphersuites to enable interoperability, reviewing implementation progress for core extensions, and discussing proposals like Slim MLS and Server Aided MLS (Split Commits) to manage the substantial bandwidth overhead introduced by post-quantum cryptography on resource-constrained mobile platforms.

