### 7. Thinking About MLS Extension Compatibility
* **Presenter:** Rowan May
* **Slides:** [Thinking about MLS extension compatibility](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/126/materials/slides-126-mls-thinking-about-mls-extension-compatibility-00)
* **Discussion:**
  * Extensibility must minimize disruption. Heavy-handed modifications, such as introducing new wire formats, break compatibility with other extensions like targeted messages. The presenter demonstrated an alternate, lighter approach using a single out-of-band AAD extension to show how features can remain highly compatible.
  * The WG was urged to design extensions that bridge the gap between deployments utilizing public commits (e.g., federated systems) and private commits. 
  * Sean Turner asked if the expired federated MLS draft should be revived. Rowan May noted that federation efforts are currently aligned with the MIMI working group, but welcomed off-list collaboration on federation interop.

